   441	  at the top of the Current phase section, mirroring the existing
   442	  9c / 9d / 9e paragraphs in voice and density.
   443	
   444	## Verification
   445	
   446	Order matters: each step assumes the previous one passed.
   447	
   448	1. **Local compose up.** From `reference/compose/`:
   449	
   450	   ```bash
   451	   cp .env.example .env
   452	   docker compose up -d --wait --wait-timeout 120
   453	   docker compose ps
   454	   ```
   455	
   456	   Expected: `postgres` and `gitea` both `running (healthy)`;
   457	   `blob-init` `exited (0)`. Then:
   458	
   459	   ```bash
   460	   docker volume ls --filter name=eden-reference_
   461	   ```
   462	
   463	   Expected: three volumes listed
   464	   (`eden-reference_eden-postgres-data`,
   465	   `eden-reference_eden-gitea-data`,
   466	   `eden-reference_eden-blob-data`).
   467	
   468	2. **Local smoke script.**
   469	
   470	   ```bash
   471	   cd reference/compose
   472	   bash healthcheck/smoke.sh
   473	   ```
   474	
   475	   Expected: prints `PASS` and exits 0.
   476	
   477	3. **Local teardown.**
   478	
   479	   ```bash
   480	   docker compose down -v
   481	   docker volume ls | grep eden-reference  # should be empty
   482	   ```
   483	
   484	4. **CI green.** All seven jobs pass on the PR
   485	   (`docs-lint`, `schema-validity`, `python-lint`,
   486	   `python-typecheck`, `python-test`, `schema-parity`,
   487	   `compose-smoke`).
   488	
   489	5. **`reference/compose/.env` is not committed.** `git status`
   490	   shows nothing under `reference/compose/.env` after running the
   491	   quickstart locally.
   492	
   493	6. **AGENTS.md, reference/README.md, docs/roadmap.md** all reflect
   494	   10a-complete state.
   495	
   496	## Execution Order
   497	
   498	1. Branch off `main` as `phase-10a/compose-infrastructure`.
   499	2. Create `reference/compose/compose.yaml`,
   500	   `reference/compose/.env.example`,
   501	   `reference/compose/healthcheck/smoke.sh` (chmod +x),
   502	   `reference/compose/README.md`.
   503	3. Update root `.gitignore`.
   504	4. Update `.github/workflows/ci.yml` with the `compose-smoke` job.
   505	5. Run local verification steps 1-3 above.
   506	6. Update `docs/roadmap.md`, `reference/README.md`, `AGENTS.md`.
   507	7. Stage + commit.
   508	8. Push + open PR.
   509	9. Wait for CI; address any failures.
   510	10. Merge once green.
   511	11. Codify any lessons learned (subagent invariants, missing
   512	    pre-flight checks, etc.) into memory or skills.
   513	
   514	## Out of Scope
   515	
   516	- Any Dockerfile for an EDEN service (`task-store-server`,
   517	  `orchestrator`, etc.). 10b.
   518	- Any `PostgresStore` Python code. Lands when its consumer lands —
   519	  10b.
   520	- Any blob storage Python code. 10d.
   521	- The `setup-experiment` script. 10c.
   522	- Gitea admin user / API token bootstrap. 10c.
   523	- Production-grade secrets management. The `.env` pattern is
   524	  developer-grade; production deployments override.
   525	- Compose overrides for the e2e test. 10e may add a `compose.test.yaml`.
   526	- Branch protection update to require `compose-smoke`. Deferred to
   527	  a follow-up after the job is proven stable.
   528	
   529	## Known Risks / Things to Watch
   530	
   531	- **GitHub Actions Docker version drift.** `ubuntu-latest` updates
   532	  Docker periodically; Compose v2 syntax we use (`--wait`,
   533	  `--wait-timeout`, `name:` top-level field, no `version:` key) all
   534	  require Docker Compose v2.20+. As of April 2026 `ubuntu-latest`
   535	  ships v2.27+, so we have margin, but if the runner ever
   536	  downgrades the smoke job will break loudly. We don't pin Docker
   537	  in CI because GitHub controls that.
   538	- **Gitea startup is slow.** First boot of `gitea/gitea:1.22.6-rootless`
   539	  takes 15-25 seconds on a cold runner. The healthcheck
   540	  `start_period: 30s` covers this; if it ever proves flaky,
   541	  the next move is bumping to 60s rather than reducing the test.
   542	- **Image-pin staleness.** `postgres:16.6-alpine` and
   543	  `gitea/gitea:1.22.6-rootless` will be superseded. We pin
   544	  deliberately; Phase 10e or a dedicated bump PR refreshes both
   545	  together when the next Compose round lands.
   546	- **Port-collision regret.** Defaults of 5433 / 3001 / 2222 sidestep
   547	  the most common collisions but a developer running their own
   548	  Gitea on 3001 will hit one. The README's Troubleshooting section
   549	  documents the `.env` overrides; no other mitigation is worth it.
   550	- **`.env.example` rotation.** The dev-only secrets in `.env.example`
   551	  are intentionally weak. If a future contributor copies them to a
   552	  real deployment they're in trouble. The README's Quickstart
   553	  section labels the values as throwaway; we additionally make
   554	  `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `GITEA_SECRET_KEY`, `GITEA_INTERNAL_TOKEN`
   555	  required-with-error-on-missing in `compose.yaml`, so production
   556	  users who delete `.env` get a clear failure rather than silently
   557	  inheriting weak defaults.
   558	- **Compose project-name leakage.** The `name: eden-reference`
   559	  field means volumes get the prefix `eden-reference_`. If a
   560	  developer also runs the predecessor's direvo monolith via
   561	  Compose, project names won't collide. If they ever rename our
   562	  `name:` field, every `docker volume ls` reference and every
   563	  `compose down -v` invocation that targets historical data will
   564	  miss the old volumes. We document the project name in the README.
   565	- **Compose v1 (`docker-compose`) users.** v1 is EOL since June
   566	  2023. Some legacy systems still ship it; those users will see
   567	  syntax errors on `name:` and `--wait`. The README's prerequisites
   568	  section names `docker compose` v2.20+ explicitly. No backcompat
   569	  shim.
   570	
   571	## Files to Reference
   572	
   573	- `direvo/Dockerfile` — predecessor's container shape, kept for
   574	  10b context but **not** copied for 10a.
   575	- `docs/roadmap.md` — Phase 10 unit definitions.
   576	- `reference/README.md` — current "Compose: Phase 10" placeholder
   577	  that this chunk updates.
   578	- The Postgres image docs (`hub.docker.com/_/postgres`) for
   579	  `POSTGRES_*` env-var semantics and `/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/`
   580	  rules.
   581	- The Gitea install docs
   582	  (`docs.gitea.com/installation/install-with-docker-rootless`) for
   583	  `GITEA__*` env-var semantics and rootless-image conventions.

